(NAMING SCOPE) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(Memos exist at three scopes:) show newline
() show newline
(Table 1: Memo Scopes) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(  Scope        Format           Authority            Visibility          ) show newline
(  core         RFC-NNN          Core maintainers     Global, canonical   ) show newline
(  federation   <fed>:memo-NNN   Federation members   Federation-wide     ) show newline
(  local        local:memo-NNN   Node author          Single node         ) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Core Scope) show newline
(----------) show newline
() show newline
(Core memos use IETF-style sequential numbering:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    Memo-001, Memo-002, ... Memo-043) show newline
() show newline
(These are canonical specifications for the Library of Cyberspace. Core) show newline
(maintainer approval required for Standards Track, BCP, and Historic.) show newline
(Anyone may pen Informational or Experimental memos with maintainer) show newline
(review.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Federation Scope) show newline
(----------------) show newline
() show newline
(Federation memos are namespaced by federation identifier:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    yoyodyne:memo-001) show newline
(    alexandria:memo-042) show newline
() show newline
(Each federation maintains its own numbering sequence. Federation memos) show newline
(are visible to all federation members but not globally canonical.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Local Scope) show newline
(-----------) show newline
() show newline
(Local memos exist only on the authoring node:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    local:memo-001) show newline
() show newline
(Local memos are drafts, notes, or node-specific documentation. They) show newline
(never leave the node unless explicitly promoted.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(PROMOTION PATH) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(Memos flow upward through scopes:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    local:memo  >  fed:memo  >  RFC) show newline
(        v            v           v) show newline
(      draft     federation    canonical) show newline
(                 review       consensus) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Local to Federation) show newline
(-------------------) show newline
() show newline
(A node author submits a local memo to their federation:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    \(memo-promote "local:memo-007" 'federation\)) show newline
(    ;; > yoyodyne:memo-023) show newline
() show newline
(Federation review and rough consensus required.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Federation to Core) show newline
(------------------) show newline
() show newline
(A federation submits a memo for core adoption:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    \(memo-promote "yoyodyne:memo-023" 'core\)) show newline
(    ;; > Memo-044 \(after consensus\)) show newline
() show newline
(Cross-federation review and rough consensus required. Standards Track) show newline
(requires core maintainer approval.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
